            <div corresp="#c0038f2">
                <head>Aleppo</head>
                <p>Mr. Conrad Schuepf, Acting Spanish Consul, charge of American interests during
                    Consul Jackson's absence. Commended by Jackson for his work.</p>
                <p>Consul Jesse B. Jackson was ordered to return to Aleppo Mar. 14, 1919 (see other
                    side); arrived May 4, 1919; took charge May 5, 1919.</p>
                <p>Consul Edward M. Groth, lately at Beirut was detailed to Aleppo for a period of
                    10 days beginning July 2, 1925. Detailed to Bagdad &amp; take charge during
                    absence of Consul Randolph on leave in U.S.A (memo of FA. dated June 3,
                    1925)</p>
            </div>
